    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "If you want to temporarily redirect stdout, you need to make sure you put the original back before closing it.\r\n\r\n```python\r\ntem = sys.stdout\r\nsys.stdout = f = open('log.txt', 'a')\r\n# ...\r\nsys.stdout = tem\r\nf.close()\r\n```\r\n\r\nIf you want to log things to a file, you might also be interested in the [%logstart magic](http://ipython.readthedocs.io/en/stable/interactive/magics.html#magic-logstart)."
